"HelpContent" : "From this page, you can see which production deployments an asset has received. Also, you can select to abort active deployments and delete or restart deployments. By default, the content on this page will refresh and update automatically (see slider icon showing On). You can force an immediate page refresh (select Refresh Now) or turn off the automatic refresh (move the slider icon from On to Off.)This page shows the name of the asset for which you are reviewing deployments. If you want to look at deployments for another asset, select Advanced Package Search and use the tools in the displayed page to select another package.The list shows all deployments for the selected asset. You can use the Filters to find specific deployment(s) for the asset. To hide or show the filter tools, select the up or down arrow beside Filters.To find specific deployments using Filters, you can do one or more of the following to narrow your search: Select the name of the asset for which you want to view its deployments. Type all or part of the name or description you know for the deployment, or name you know for the package. If you type only a partial Deployment Name, Deployment Description, or Package Name, select where that partial string falls in the full search string. Specify a time/date range for when the deployment was started. Specify the current status of the deployment you want to view. Started ? deployment was started Created ? deployment was created but has not yet been run Aborted ? deployment was cancelled or stopped before completing Completed ? deployment executing completed as designed Failed ? deployment was started and failed before completing Select the name of the user who started the deployment. When you?re finished setting filters, click Filter to apply them and see the related deployments. Selecting Clear will remove all filters.The Deployments list updates to show all deployments executed for the selected asset. To view the assets for a deployment, do the following: If you want to view details for a deployment, double-click or select the deployment and the View information for deployment icon above the list. After viewing this information you can select Back to return to the Track Deployment By Asset page. To delete a deployment Click the deployment and select the Delete icon above the list. In the Delete Deployment? message, select Yes. When the list refreshes you?ll see that the deployment has been removed To restart a deployment Click the deployment and select the Restart icon above the list. Note that you can only restart deployments with status values of: Aborted, Canceled, Completed, Failed. In the Restart Deployment? message, select Yes. When the list refreshes you?ll see that the Status column for the deployment is updated to show Started. To abort a deployment Click the deployment and select the Abort icon above the list. Note that you can only abort deployments with status values of: Started. In the Abort Deployment? message, select Yes. When the list refreshes you?ll see that the Status column for the deployment is updated to show Aborted.
